<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="441" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1443,913,1947]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">
<emphasis box="[151,372,913,939]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Female macroptera</emphasis>
. Body dark brown, all femora and tibiae dark brown, fore tarsi yellowish brown, mid and hind tarsi brown (
<figureCitation box="[298,365,948,974]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[175,1409,191,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[165,1421,179,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. (1) Psephenothrips uttarakhandensis sp. n. Female; (2) Neohydatothrips xestosternitus, Female. Psephenothrips uttarakhandensis, Female, 3–7: (3) Head and pronotum; (4) Tergites IX–X; (5) Prosternum; (6) Pelta; (7) Antenna." pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Antennal segments I–II, VII–VIII brown; III yellow; IV–V yellow with brown apically; VI brown with yellow basally. Fore wings pale with brown basally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1443,913,1947]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">
Head longer than broad (
<figureCitation box="[490,560,1017,1043]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[175,1409,191,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[165,1421,179,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. (1) Psephenothrips uttarakhandensis sp. n. Female; (2) Neohydatothrips xestosternitus, Female. Psephenothrips uttarakhandensis, Female, 3–7: (3) Head and pronotum; (4) Tergites IX–X; (5) Prosternum; (6) Pelta; (7) Antenna." pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); dorsal surface with tranverse anastomosing straie; Postocular setae longer than eyes, blunt apically; cheeks weakly rounded with four minute setae; maxillary stylets very long, reaching eyes, almost touching each other. Eyes 0.29–0.35 times as long as head. Mouthcone long, touching almost the level of anterior margin of ferna. Antennae 8-segmented; III with one sense cone and VI with three sense cones; VIII shorter than VII (
<figureCitation box="[262,331,1156,1182]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[175,1409,191,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[165,1421,179,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. (1) Psephenothrips uttarakhandensis sp. n. Female; (2) Neohydatothrips xestosternitus, Female. Psephenothrips uttarakhandensis, Female, 3–7: (3) Head and pronotum; (4) Tergites IX–X; (5) Prosternum; (6) Pelta; (7) Antenna." pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Pronotum 2.1–2.3 times as broad as long, surface smooth with a short median longitudinal line; with five pairs of major setae, long, blunt apically (
<figureCitation box="[716,782,1191,1217]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[175,1409,191,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[165,1421,179,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. (1) Psephenothrips uttarakhandensis sp. n. Female; (2) Neohydatothrips xestosternitus, Female. Psephenothrips uttarakhandensis, Female, 3–7: (3) Head and pronotum; (4) Tergites IX–X; (5) Prosternum; (6) Pelta; (7) Antenna." pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); posteroangular setae longest, almost as long as pronotum length. Mesopraesternum boat shaped (
<figureCitation box="[601,672,1225,1252]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[175,1409,191,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[165,1421,179,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. (1) Psephenothrips uttarakhandensis sp. n. Female; (2) Neohydatothrips xestosternitus, Female. Psephenothrips uttarakhandensis, Female, 3–7: (3) Head and pronotum; (4) Tergites IX–X; (5) Prosternum; (6) Pelta; (7) Antenna." pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Metanotum weakly reticulate; metathoracic sternopleural sutures absent. Fore wing with 21–24 duplicated cilia, with three basal setae, blunt apically. Pelta with polygonal reticulation (
<figureCitation box="[210,278,1295,1321]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[175,1409,191,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[165,1421,179,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. (1) Psephenothrips uttarakhandensis sp. n. Female; (2) Neohydatothrips xestosternitus, Female. Psephenothrips uttarakhandensis, Female, 3–7: (3) Head and pronotum; (4) Tergites IX–X; (5) Prosternum; (6) Pelta; (7) Antenna." pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Abdominal tergite IX with S1 and S2 setae narrowly blunt and 0.6–0.8 times as long as the tube. Tube shorter than head, and anal setae subequal to tube (
<figureCitation box="[721,790,1329,1355]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[175,1409,191,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[165,1421,179,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. (1) Psephenothrips uttarakhandensis sp. n. Female; (2) Neohydatothrips xestosternitus, Female. Psephenothrips uttarakhandensis, Female, 3–7: (3) Head and pronotum; (4) Tergites IX–X; (5) Prosternum; (6) Pelta; (7) Antenna." pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1443,913,1947]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,1364,1390]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Measurements.</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[397,497,1364,1390]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">holotype</typeStatus>
female in microns). Body length 3524. Dorsal head length 320, across cheeks 250; compound eye dorsal length (width) 93(68); postocular seta length 124. Pronotum median width (length) 381 (163). Anteroangular setae 53, anteromarginal setae 35, midlateral setae 88–91, posteroangular setae 150, epimeral setae 115. Antennal segments I–VIII length (width): 42 (45), 53 (38), 90 (36), 91 (44), 80 (36), 71 (35), 59 (29), 39 (13). Fore wing basal setae length S1 92, S2 115, S3 115. Pelta length (width at base) 139 (260); tergite X setae S1 190–196; tube length 257, width at base 98, at apex 44; anal setae length 254–257.
</paragraph>
