<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="443" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1443,913,1947]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="443" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1745,1771]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Comments</emphasis>
. According to the key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Tyagi, K. &amp; Kumar, V." box="[653,951,1745,1772]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" pagination="281 - 287" refId="ref2888" refString="Tyagi, K. &amp; Kumar, V. (2012) A new species of Psephenothrips (Thysanoptera: Phlaeothripidae) from India. Oriental Insects 46, 281 - 287. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.2012.752618" type="journal article" year="2012">Tyagi and Kumar (2012)</bibRefCitation>
as well as 
<bibRefCitation author="Dang, L. - H. &amp; Zhao, L. - P. &amp; Li, Y. - Q. &amp; Qiao, G. - X." box="[1100,1328,1745,1772]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" pagination="113 - 121" refId="ref2419" refString="Dang, L. - H., Zhao, L. - P., Li, Y. - Q. &amp; Qiao, G. - X. (2021) Studies on the genus Psephenothrips Reyes from China (Thysanoptera, Phlaeothripinae), with one new species. ZooKeys, 1029, 113 - 121. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 1029.64531" type="journal article" year="2021">
Dang 
<emphasis box="[1174,1230,1745,1771]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">et al</emphasis>
. (2021)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Patidar &amp; Singha &amp; Kumar &amp; Tyagi, 2022" authorityName="Patidar &amp; Singha &amp; Kumar &amp; Tyagi" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Psephenothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uttarakhandensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Psephenothrips uttarakhandensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[465,536,1780,1806]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[465,536,1780,1806]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Okajima" authorityYear="2006" box="[689,844,1780,1807]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Psephenothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptoceras">
<emphasis box="[689,706,1781,1806]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[727,844,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">leptoceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moulton" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[912,1034,1780,1807]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Psephenothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="machili">
<emphasis box="[912,929,1781,1806]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[950,1034,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">machili</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It can be differentiated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Okajima" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Psephenothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptoceras">
<emphasis box="[1412,1429,1781,1806]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,268,1815,1841]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">leptoceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of metathoracic sternopleural sutures (distinct metathoracic sternopleural sutures are present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Okajima" authorityYear="2006" box="[395,546,1849,1875]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Psephenothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptoceras">
<emphasis box="[395,546,1849,1875]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">P. leptoceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), antennal segment VIII shorter than VII (VIII longer than VII in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Okajima" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Psephenothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptoceras">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">P. leptoceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), posteroangular setae longer than epimerals (subequal to epimerals in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Okajima" authorityYear="2006" box="[1118,1271,1884,1910]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Psephenothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptoceras">
<emphasis box="[1118,1271,1884,1910]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">P. leptoceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), anteroangular setae longer than the anteromarginals (anteroangular setae subequal to anteromarginals in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Okajima" authorityYear="2006" box="[1270,1420,1920,1946]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Psephenothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptoceras">
<emphasis box="[1270,1420,1920,1946]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">P. leptoceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The new species is also differentiated by 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moulton" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[609,724,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Psephenothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="machili">
<emphasis box="[609,626,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="443">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[640,724,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="443">machili</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by fore tibiae colour (brown in the new species versus brown in basal ½ and pale in apical ½ in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moulton" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[508,620,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Psephenothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="machili">
<emphasis box="[508,620,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="443">P. machili</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), postocular setae (longer than eyes in the new species versus as long as or shorter than eyes in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moulton" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[411,523,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Psephenothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="machili">
<emphasis box="[411,523,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="443">P. machili</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and posteroangular setae (as long as the length of the pronotum versus half the length of the pronotum in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moulton" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[444,556,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Psephenothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="machili">
<emphasis box="[444,556,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="443">P. machili</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
